summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions 1528 (2004), 1572 (2004), 1584 (2005), and 1594 (2005), 
Reaffirming commitment to C么te d'Ivoire's sovereignty, independence, territorial integrity, and unity, 
Recalling endorsement of Linas-Marcoussis and Accra III Agreements,
Welcoming efforts of Secretary-General, African Union, and Economic Community of West African States, 
Determining the situation in C么te d'Ivoire poses a threat to international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter,
1. Welcomes the Pretoria Agreement signed on 6 April 2005, 
commends President Thabo Mbeki's role, and reaffirms support for his mediation efforts;
2. Calls on parties to implement the Pretoria Agreement, 
reminding them to refer differences to President Thabo Mbeki;
3. Welcomes decision on eligibility for Presidency, 
notes President Laurent Gbagbo's announcement on 26 April 2005;
4. Urges parties to ensure free, fair, and transparent general elections;
5. Extends mandate of UN Operation in C么te d'Ivoire and French forces until 4 June 2005;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
